            "attachments": [
                {
                    "id": 1,
                    "footer_icon": "https:\/\/slack.github.com\/static\/img\/favicon-neutral.png",
                    "ts": 1732374714,
                    "color": "6f42c1",
                    "fallback": "[fuse-open\/fuselibs] Pull request opened by ichan-mb",
                    "text": "On Android, when toying with `Video` Control using `Progress` property and bind it with Sliders Value, because of the two-way binding, the Sliders value always keep Progress value of Video control to restart from beginning so that the video wont play. To fix the issue, we only dispatch notification of progress changes only when triggered by user and not by the value binding.\n\ntest case:\n\n```\n&lt;DockPanel&gt;\n  &lt;Slider ux:Name=\"_slider\" Minimum=\"0\" Maximum=\"1\" Dock=\"Top\" \/&gt;\n  &lt;Video ux:Name=\"_video\" StretchMode=\"Fill\" IsLooping=\"true\" Url=\"https:\/\/storage.googleapis.com\/gtv-videos-bucket\/sample\/BigBuckBunny.mp4\" Progress=\"{Property _slider.Value}\"&gt;\n&lt;\/DockPanel&gt;\n\n```\n\nThis PR contains:\n\n• Changelog\n• Documentation\n• Tests",
                    "pretext": "Pull request opened by <https:\/\/github.com\/ichan-mb|ichan-mb>",
                    "title": "<https:\/\/github.com\/fuse-open\/fuselibs\/pull\/1504|#1504 Native Slider Android: fix bug recursive setting value>",
